l]]\n|[[Linebacker|LB]]\n|[[Missouri Tigers football|Missouri]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ADD8E6 | [[Jakobi Meyers]]\n|WR\n|[[NC State Wolfpack football|NC State]]\n|-\n|[[D'Angelo Ross]]\n|[[Cornerback|CB]]\n|[[New Mexico Lobos football|New Mexico]]\n|-\n|[[Tyree St. Louis]]\n|OT\n|Miami\n|-\n|[[Xavier Ubosi]]\n|WR\n|[[UAB Blazers football|UAB]]\n|May 6, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patriots.com/news/patriots-sign-wr-xavier-ubosi|title=Patriots Sign WR Xavier Ubosi|website=www.patriots.com|language=en-US|access-date=2019-05-07}}</ref>\n|-\n|style=\"background:#ADD8E6 | [[Gunner Olszewski]]\n|WR\n|[[Bemidji State Beavers football|Bemidji State]]\n|May 22, 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.patriots.com/news/patriots-sign-rookie-wr-gunner-olszewski|title=Patriots Sign Rookie WR Gunner Olszewski|website=www.patriots.com|language=en-US|access-date=May 24, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Martez Ivey]]\n|OT\n|[[Florida Gators football|Florida]]\n|July 30, 2019<ref name=\"Patriots sign OL Martez Ivey; relea\"/>\n|}\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n| style=\"background:#ADD8E6; width:20px; em\"| \n| Made regular season roster\n|}\n\n===Suspensions===\n*[[Tight end]] [[Benjamin Watson]] was suspended for four games at the start of the season for failing a drug test from March.<ref>{{cite web|last=Abdeldaiem|first=Alaa|title=Benjamin Watson Announces Four-Game Suspension for Violating NFL's Drug Policy|url=https://www.si.com/nfl/2019/05/26/benjamin-watson-announces-suspension-violation-ped-policy|date=May 26, 2019|website=SI.com|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*Tight end [[Lance Kendricks]] was suspended for the season-opener by violating the league's policy on substances of abuse.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bergman |first1=Jeremy |title=Patriots TE Lance Kendricks suspended one game |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001043953/article/patriots-te-lance-kendricks-suspended-one-game |website=NFL.com |accessdate=August 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Injuries===\n*May 8: [[Wide receiver]] [[Bruce Ellington]] was released with an injury designation.<ref name=\"patriots.com\"/>\n*July 25: Wide receiver [[Julian Edelman]] injured his thumb playing catch a few weeks prior. He would be set to miss \"a few weeks\" including possibly all of preseason.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bird |first1=Hayden |title=Morning sports update: Julian Edelman is set to miss \u2018a few weeks\u2019 with a broken thumb |url=https://www.boston.com/sports/new-england-patriots/2019/07/25/julian-edelman-broken-thumb-injury-update |website=Boston.com |accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref> He returned on August 19, just before Week 3 of preseason.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Gordon |first1=Grant |title=Patriots' Julian Edelman passes physical, off NFI list|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001042830/article/patriots-julian-edelman-passes-physical-off-nfi-list |website=NFL.com |accessdate=August 19, 2019}}</ref>\n*August 8: Wide receiver [[N'Keal Harry]] suffered an ankle injury during training camp and a \"minor\" hamstring injury while going up for a catch in the Patriots' first preseason game against the [[2019 Detroit Lions season|Detroit Lions]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Leger |first1=Justin |title=N'Keal Harry injury: Patriots rookie reportedly not expected to miss Week 1 |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/boston/patriots/nkeal-harry-injury-patriots-rookie-reportedly-not-expected-miss-week-1 |website=NBCSports.com |accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> He was placed on [[injured reserve]] on September 2, 2019 after missing multiple weeks of practice.<ref name=\"ThomasHarRy\"/>\n*August 12: [[Cornerback]] [[D'Angelo Ross]] was waived with an injury designation. The following day, he was placed on the injury report after having cleared waivers.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cox|first=Zach|title=Patriots Training Camp Standout Reverts To Injured Reserve After Clearing Waivers|url=https://nesn.com/2019/08/patriots-training-camp-standout-reverts-to-injured-reserve-after-clearing-waivers/|date=August 13, 2019|website=NESN.com|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}</ref>\n*August 15: Wide receiver [[Maurice Harris (American football)|Maurice Harris]] sustained a leg injury in the Patriots' first joint practice with the [[2019 Tennessee Titans season|Tennessee Titans]]. His recovery period was described as \"a while\".<ref>{{cite web |last1=Callahan |first1=Andrew |title=Patriots WR Maurice Harris may be out \u2018a while\u2019 with leg injury (Report) |url=https://www.masslive.com/patriots/2019/08/patriots-wr-maurice-harris-may-be-out-a-while-with-leg-injury-report.html |website=MassLive.com |accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> Although, while still limited by his injury, he returned on August 20 after missing only a few days.<ref>{{cite web |title=Patriots' Maurice Harris: Returns in some Capacity |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/patriots-maurice-harris-returns-in-some-capacity/ |website=CBSSports.com |accessdate=August 20, 2019}}</ref> Ultimately, he was released with an injury designation on August 25. He was placed on the injury report the next day after clearing waivers.<ref name=\"KeiontaDavisHarris\">{{cite web |last1=Buchmasser |first1=Bernd |title=Maurice Harris and Keionta Davis clear waivers, revert to the Patriots\u2019 injured reserve list |url=https://www.patspulpit.com/2019/8/26/20834184/maurice-harris-keionta-davis-clear-waivers-revert-to-new-england-patriots-injured-reserve-list |website=PatsPulpit.com |accessdate=August 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*August 17: Defensive end [[Derek Rivers]] suffered a leg injury during the Patriots' Week 2 preseason game against the Tennessee Titans.<ref>{{cite web |last1=O'Malley |first1=Nick |title=Derek Rivers injury: New England Patriots DE leaves game in first quarter |url=https://www.masslive.com/patriots/2019/08/derek-rivers-injury-new-england-patriots-de-leaves-game-in-first-quarter.html |website=MassLive.com |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve week later.<ref name=\"ABC243\" />\n*August 25: [[Defensive end]] [[Keionta Davis]] was placed on the injury report.<ref name=\"KeiontaDavisHarris\" />\n*August 25: [[Outside linebacker]] [[Brandon King (safety)|Brandon King]] suffered torn quadriceps in the Patriots' preseason game against the [[2019 Carolina Panthers season|Carolina Panthers]]. He was placed on injured reserve days later.<ref>{{cite web |title=Patriots' Brandon King: Placed on IR |url=https://www.cbssports.com/fantasy/football/news/patriots-brandon-king-placed-on-ir/ |website=CBSSports.com |accessdate=August 27, 2019}}</ref>\n*August 31: [[Center (American football)|Center]] [[David Andrews (American football)|David Andrews]] was diagnosed with a blood clot in his lungs on August 26.<ref>{{cite web |title=David Andrews hospitalized with blood clot |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001044490/article/patriots-c-david-andrews-hospitalized-with-blood-clot |website=NFL.com |accessdate=August 26, 2019}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve days later.<ref name=\"ABC243\" />\n*August 31: Wide receiver [[Cameron Meredith]] was kept on the [[physically unable to perform list]], still dealing with issues with his knee from an [[Anterior cruciate ligament|ACL]] injury he suffered during the [[2017 NFL season]].<ref name=\"ABC243\" />\n*August 31: [[Offensive guard]] [[Hjalte Froholdt]] was placed on injured reserve as a result of the neck injury he sustained during Week 4 of preseason against the [[2019 New York Giants season|New York Giants]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Alper |first1=Josh |title=Patriots put Hjalte Froholdt, Derek Rivers on injured reserve |url=https://profootballtalk.nbcsports.com/2019/08/31/patriots-put-hjalte-froholdt-derek-rivers-on-injured-reserve/ |website=ProFootballTalk.NBCSports.com |accessdate=August 31, 2019}}</ref>\n*August 31: [[Strong safety]] [[Malik Gant]] was placed on injured reserve.<ref name=\"ABC243\" />\n*September 8: [[Offensive tackle]] [[Marcus Cannon]] suffered a shoulder injury against the [[2019 Pittsburgh Steelers season|Pittsburgh Steelers]] during the fourth quarter of the Week 1 matchup. The injury will be a setback for the Patriots' offensive line, although not season-ending for Cannon.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Buchmasser |first1=Bernd |title=Injury update: Patriots right tackle Marcus Cannon\u2019s shoulder injury reportedly not considered a long-term issue |url=https://www.patspulpit.com/2019/9/10/20858730/injury-update-new-england-patriots-right-tackle-marcus-cannons-shoulder-no-long-term-issue |website=PatsPulpit.com |accessdate=September 10, 2019}}</ref>\n*September 15: Offensive tackle [[Isaiah Wynn]] sustained a toe injury in the Patriots' Week 2 game against the [[2019 Miami Dolphins season|Miami Dolphins]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Injuries: Michael Gallup (knee) to miss 2 to 4 weeks |url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001055662/article/injuries-pats-isaiah-wynn-to-have-mri-on-injured-toe |website=NFL.com |publisher=NFL |accessdate=September 16, 2019|date=September 16, 2019}}</ref> He was placed on injured reserve on September 17, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|work=NFL.com|url=http://www.nfl.com/news/story/0ap3000001056112/article/patriots-place-ot-isaiah-wynn-toe-on-injured-reserve|title=Patriots place OT Isaiah Wynn (toe) on injured reserve|date=September 17, 2019|accessdate=September 17, 2019}}</ref>\n*September 22: Julian Edelman suffered a rib injury in the Patriots' Week 3 game against the [[2019 New York Jets season|New York Jets]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=London |first1=Adam |title=Julian Edelman Injury: Here's Latest Update On Patriots Wide Receiver |url=https://nesn.com/2019/09/julian-edelman-injury-heres-latest-update-on-patriots-wide-receiver/ |website=NESN.com |publisher=NESN |accessdate=September 22, 2019|date=September 22, 2019}}</ref>\n*September 23: [[Fullback (gridiron football)|Fullback]] [[James Develin]] was placed on injured reserve due to a neck injury he suffered in Week 2 against the Miami Dolphins and is set to be out for at least 8 weeks.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kyed |first1=Doug |title=Patriots Place Fullback James Develin On Injured Reserve With Neck Ailment |url=https://nesn.com/2019/09/patriots-place-fullback-james-develin-on-injured-reserve-with-neck-ailment/ |website=NESN.com |publisher=NESN |accessdate=September 23, 2019|date=September 23, 2019}}</ref>\n*October 2: [[Placekicker|Kicker]] [[Stephen Gostkowski]] was placed on injured reserve as a result of a left hip injury.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Buchmasser |first1=Bernd |title=Patriots place kicker Stephen Gostkowski on injured reserve |url=https://www.patspulpit.com/2019/10/2/20895566/breaking-new-england-patriots-place-kicker-stephen-gostkowski-on-injured-reserve |website=PatsPulpit.com |publisher=Pats Pulpit |accessdate=October 2, 2019|date=October 2, 2019}}</ref>\n*October 14: Fullback [[Jakob Johnson]] was placed on injured reserve due to a shoulder injury he suffered in Week 5 against the [[2019 Washington Redskins season|Washington Redskins]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Patriots Place FB Jakob Johnson on IR|url=https://www.patriots.com/news/patriots-place-fb-jakob-johnson-on-ir|website=Patriots.com|date=October 14, 2019}}</ref>\n*October 23: Wide receiver [[Josh Gordon]] was placed due to a knee injury he suffered in Week 6 against the [[2019 New York Giants season|New York Giants]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/27912736/patriots-josh-gordon-lands-ir|last=Reiss|first=Mike|title=Patriots' Josh Gordon lands on IR|date=October 23, 2019|work=ESPN}}</ref>\n*November 19: Wide receiver [[Gunner Olszewski]] was placed on injured reserve with ankle and hamstring injuries.<ref>{{cite web|title=Patriots activate OL Isaiah Wynn; Place WR Gunner Olszewski on IR|url=https://www.patriots.com/news/patriots-activate-ol-isaiah-wynn-place-wr-gunner-olszewski-on-ir|website=Patriots.com|date=November 19, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Staff==\n{{NFL final staff\n|Year=2019\n|TeamName=New England Patriots\n|Front Office=\n*Chairman/CEO \u2013